Vice President Kamala Harris delivered a speech at the South Carolina State House, honoring the legacy of Martin Luther King Jr. She discussed the current threats to freedom in America, including attacks on voting rights, restrictions on reproductive rights, lack of gun safety laws, discrimination against LGBTQ individuals, and efforts to rewrite history. Harris emphasized the importance of young leaders in the fight for freedom and called on Americans to continue the struggle for justice and equality. She ended her speech by quoting Coretta Scott King and expressing hope for a better future.